# Resolution 2004-08-10.iwj.dbg.3: Board Advisors

August 10th, 2004

This resolution was adopted by the Board of Directors of SPI at their
meeting of [August 10, 2004](/meetings/minutes/2004/2004-08-10).

This resolution supersedes resolutions
[2003-07-26.bmh.1](../../2003/2003-07-26.bmh.1),
[2002-05-07.mgs.3.br](../../2002/2002-05-07.mgs.3.br),
[2001-05-16.nl](../../2001/2001-05-16.nl),
[1999-08-12.iwj.1](../../1999/1999-08-12.iwj.1) &
[1998-09-25.nl.1](../../1998/1998-09-25.nl.1).

### Whereas

* SPI aims to further the interests of its Associated Projects;
  Associated Projects are not necessarily represented on
  SPI's Board of Directors;
* The SPI Board may appoint or remove Board Advisors as it sees fit;

### The Board of Directors of SPI resolves that

* The Board hereby creates the position of Representative Advisor
  and offers one Representative Advisor seat to a
  representative from each active Associated Project.
* Each Representative Advisor will be nominated and recalled
  at the discretion of the Associated Project being represented.
* Each Representative Advisor is an Advisor by virtue of their
  nomination by the Associated Project, without further resolution
  of the SPI Board.
* The SPI Board reserves the right to vary the number of
  Representative Advisor seats it offers to a particular Associated
  Project. The SPI Board also reserves the right to reject,
  remove, or replace a Project's nominee(s), should the need arise.

### Furthermore the Board reconfirms that

* Unless stated otherwise, Advisors appointed directly by resolution
  of the Board shall serve a term of one year from the date of their
  appointment, and may be renewed in the same manner they were
  appointed an unlimited number of times;
* All Advisors shall be included on the Board mailing list, have
  the right to attend all Board meetings, and to propose and speak
  to, but not vote on, Board resolutions. Advisors may not speak on
  behalf of SPI without the explicit permission of the Board.

